data.text:
Scott’s desire to tell people what movies to watch knows no bounds. He’s decided to create a series on here devoted to profiling directors and creating guides to their films. This week’s director is… Tim Burton.

Highly recommended: Batman, Edward Scissorhands, Batman Returns, Ed Wood

Recommended: Pee-Wee’s Big Adventure, Beetlejuice, Sleepy Hollow, Big Fish, Big Eyes

Worth a look: Corpse Bride (partially directed by Burton), Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street, Frankenweenie, Miss Peregrine’s Home for Peculiar Children

Approach with caution: Dark Shadows

Not recommended: Mars Attacks!, Planet of the Apes, Alice in Wonderland, Dumbo

Next week’s director is… Louis Malle!
